      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 131: Any non-empty translation removes type\u003d\"unfinished\" without validating Qt placeholders or accelerator/markup preservation. A malformed JSON entry can silently break runtime formatting, e.g. dropping %1 from a source that uses arg(), or breaking rich-text tags. Transifex previously helped enforce this class of checks; the in-house importer should reject unsafe translations before writing. Add validation in the resolver path before patching, for example compare placeholder sets from source and translation and fail with a clear ValueError when they differ.",
